By Boluwatife Ezekiel Olaleye
Reports says Boko Haram insurgents have killed three people and set fire to scores of homes in a raid targeting vulnerable rural communities in northeast Nigeria on Thursday.
Modu Ganamani, Information Officer for the Guzamala Local Government Area in Northern Borno state, said the attack happened at about 3pm on Wednesday.
“Boko Haram insurgents came in large numbers in trucks and on motorcycles and attacked Goram and two neighbouring villages, Lingis and Ajidari, ” he said.
